<TITLE> MP withdraws from Bhola by-election </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bhola, Apr 8 (bdnews24.com)  The former MP of Bhola-3 Md Jasimuddin, whose election to the constituency in the 2008 election was deemed unlawful, withdrew his nomination paper on Thursday for the forthcoming by-election . District election officer Md Hasanuzzaman said Jasim had faxed the application for withdrawing his nomination to the district returning officer. Thursday was the deadline for withdrawal. AL's Nurunnabi Chowdhury Shaon and BNP's Hafizuddin Ahmed will now be the main rivals in the polls to be held on Apr 24. ELECTION COORDINATOR TOFAIL Meanwhile, senior AL leader Tofael Ahmed was made the chief coordinator for the election, AL deputy office secretary Mrinal Kanti Das told bdnews24.com on Thursday night. Party general secretary Syed Ashraful Islam wrote to Tofail about the decision taken by the party chief Sheikh Hasina, he added. Tofail, who is the member of AL's advisory council, has been given the responsibility to try and ensure victory for the AL candidate and to maintain discipline within the party during the election. The letter added that joint secretary general Mahbubul Alam Hanif will assist Tofail. EC IN BHOLA Election commissioner M Shakhawat Hossain is set to visit the constituency on Friday. During his three-day visit Shakhawat will meet the district election officers and officials of the law enforcing agencies. He will also visit five vulnerable voting centres at Char Zahiruddin under Tazumuddin upazila. A total of 2,23,926 voters will vote at 86 poll centres in the constituency. The government on Apr 4 decided to deploy from Apr 21.a joint force of RAB and armed police bdnews24.com/c
